description: "Tap Tap." When Batman sets out to trap a thief in the home of a billionaire investment banker, he falls afoul of a security system far more elaborate than he expected. Featuring...Catwoman!
name: Tap Tap, Part 1 of 1

description:
Spider-Man and the Human Torch are trapped on a space station ful of Octo-Zombies plummeting toward the Earth! The best buds super team-up is running out of air and running out of time!

Also, all hell breaks lose as Spidey teams-up with the Spirit of Vengeance, Ghost Rider!

Plus, it’s all-out classic action as Spider-Man battles the NEW Sinister Six in a desperate fight to stop Doc Ock’s insane scheme to take over the world! ‘Nuff Said!

Story and art by Dan Slott, Christopher Yost, Guiseppe Camuncoli, Rob Williams, Lee Garbett, David Michelinie and Erik Larsen!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #681, Amazing Spider-Man/Ghost Rider: Motorstorm and Amazing Spider-Man #338!

Shocking past of Tony Stark!

This issue contains: second half of Invincible Iron Man Annual #1 and Invincible Iron Man #500.1
name: Мандарин. Моя история. Часть 2; Железный Человек. Новое начало

description:
Legendary spy returns! Whose side is Nick Fury?

So begins the Avengers!

This issue contains: Avengers (V.4) #9, New Avengers (V.2) #9
name: Issue #12

description: Woody, Buzz, and the gang encounter a mysterious egg-shaped toy. They crash Andy's science fair in a heroic effort to repair his broken exhibit. The toys must make peace with the family's new dog, Buster. And finally, Mr. Potato Head decides that he's tired of being just an inanimate toy. He's going to reveal his true nature to Andy. Can Woody stop him before it's too late?

Anti-Venom returns!

This issue contains: Amazing Spider-Man #662 & #663
